{"updated_at": "2012-07-26T10:15:24Z", "repo": "rails", "created_at": "2012-07-26T10:15:24Z", "owner": "rails", "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/comments/7273953", "id": 7273953, "issue_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/3023", "issue_id": 3023, "user": {"repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/morgoth/repos", "type": "User", "html_url": "https://github.com/morgoth", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/morgoth/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/morgoth/subscriptions", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/morgoth/following{/other_user}", "gravatar_id": "8085138938c34ae1af140bfc91f2fe56", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/morgoth/orgs", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/morgoth", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/morgoth/gists{/gist_id}", "avatar_url": "https://0.gravatar.com/avatar/8085138938c34ae1af140bfc91f2fe56?d=https%3A%2F%2Fidenticons.github.com%2F6cc6e45d2f9cf66facfacd3554b52577.png", "id": 10766, "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/morgoth/events{/privacy}", "login": "morgoth", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/morgoth/received_events", "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/morgoth/followers"}, "body": "I never used that feature, so it's hard to me talk about pros, but I'm seeing some downsides:\n\n```ruby\n# STI: Coach < Person\ncoach = Coach.last\ncoach.first_name = \"John\"\ncoach.changed?\n# => true\ncoach.becomes(Person).changed?\n# => false\n```\nThis one doesn't make sense, however it's possible:\n\n```ruby\npost = Post.last\ncomment = post.becomes(Comment)\ncomment.persisted?\n# => true\ncomment.reload\n# comment is now record from comments table (with the same id as post)\n```", "_id": {"$oid": "523f90c1bd354364b9018dab"}, "html_url": "https://github.com/rails/rails/pull/3023#issuecomment-7273953"}
